message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Dominica in the past five years was the devastation caused by Hurricane Maria in September 2017. The Category 5 hurricane struck the island, causing widespread destruction and loss of life. It resulted in the destruction of infrastructure, homes, and public facilities, leaving the island in a state of emergency. The impact of Hurricane Maria was profound, with the country facing significant challenges in terms of recovery and rebuilding.
